<title type="html"><![CDATA[8/12(Thu.)Buildings give people headaches/Chef says climate change can be tackled, the way from your momma (Danny)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=531&amp;p=554#p554"><![CDATA[
08/12(Thu.)Looking at buildings can actually give people headaches. Here's why/Chef says climate change can be tackled if you cook the way your momma (really) did (Host:Danny)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1 Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Presentation 1<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40: Session 2 Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Presentation 2<br /><br />At the presentation, the time limit is 1-2 minutes for each speaker.<br /><br />Let's join the Zoom meeting this Thursday at 07:00 pm<br /><a href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw#success" class="postlink">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw#success</a><br /><br />會議 ID:929 8726 6213<br />密碼:112233<br /><br />-----------------------------------------------------------------<br />Article1: Looking at buildings can actually give people headaches. Here's why<br /><a href="https://edition.cnn.com/style/article/why-looking-at-buildings-can-give-people-headaches/index.html" class="postlink">https://edition.cnn.com/style/article/why-looking-at-buildings-can-give-people-headaches/index.html</a><br />1. What are your thoughts after reading the article?<br />2. What is your ideal building? Is it in nature?<br />3. Apart from buildings, what do you think are the essentials of a good life?<br /><br />-------------------------------------------------------------------<br />Article2: Chef says climate change can be tackled if you cook the way your momma (really) did<br /><a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2021/07/25/us/sustainable-eating-camilla-marcus-climate-weir-wellness/index.html" class="postlink">https://edition.cnn.com/2021/07/25/us/sustainable-eating-camilla-marcus-climate-weir-wellness/index.html</a><br />1. What do you think the momma cook referred to in the article means?<br />2. Do you have any stereotypes about Western eating habits in your mind?<br />3. How do you think this article will affect Taiwanese people? Why? Why not?<br /><br />extra reading:Climate change: Where we are in seven charts and what you can do to help<br /><a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-46384067" class="postlink">https://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-46384067</a><br /><br />-----------------------------------------------------------------<br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=12531">Danny Lin</a> — Mon Aug 09, 2021 1:22 pm</p><hr />
